Art in the Streets is an annual street festival that recently took place at the heart of Nairobi’s Central Business District, Koinange street. The event showcases socially conscious East African Art, Music and Creativity.  It also acts as a platform for innovative young artists to showcase their creative genius though visual and performance quality pieces, including public installations, film screenings, photography exhibitions, music, poetry and literary readings. Participants this year included Band Beca, Drum Doctor, Fadhili, Goofy, Ian Msanii, Kapedo and Miss Kuria.